quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  19,52,"We called him from the right side of the Mount and We drew him near [to Ourselves] for confidential discourse"
  19,53,"And We gave him out of Our mercy his brother Aaron, a prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the Book Ishmael. Indeed, he was true to his promise, and an apostle and prophet"
  19,55,"He used to bid his family to [maintain] the prayer and to [pay] the zakat, and was pleasing to his Lord"
  19,56,"And mention in the Book Idrees. Indeed, he was a truthful one and a prophet"
  19,57,and We raised him to an exalted station
  19,58,"They are the ones whom Allah has blessed from among the prophets of Adam’s progeny, and from [the progeny of] those We carried with Noah, and from among the progeny of Abraham and Israel, and from among those that We guided and chose. When the signs of the All-beneficent were recited to them, they would fall down weeping in prostration"
  19,59,"But they were succeeded by an evil posterity who neglected the prayer, and followed [their base] appetites. So they will soon encounter [the reward of] perversity"
  19,60,"barring those who repent, believe, and act righteously. Such will enter paradise, and they will not be wronged in the least"
  19,61,"Gardens of Eden promised by the All-beneficent to His servants, [while they were still] unseen. Indeed His promise is bound to come to pass"
  19,62,"Therein they will not hear vain talk, but only ‘Peace!’ Therein they will have their provision morning and evening"
  19,63,This is the paradise We will give as inheritance to those of Our servants who are Godwary
  19,64,"[O Gabriel, tell the Prophet,] ‘We do not descend except by the command of your Lord. To Him belongs whatever is before us and whatever is behind us and whatever is in between that, and your Lord does not forget"